GOODWILL IMPAIRMENT

WE CONDUCTED OUR ANNUAL GOODWILL IMPAIRMENT TEST AS OF MAY 1, 2012 FOR ALL REPORTING UNITS. THIS TEST, WHICH WAS BASED ON OUR

MOST RECENT CASH FLOW FORECAST, INDICATED THAT OSDS CARRYING VALUE EXCEEDED ITS ESTIMATED FAIR VALUE. ACCORDINGLY, WE RECORDED A NON-CASH, NON-TAX DEDUCTIBLE GOODWILL IMPAIRMENT CHARGE OF $6.2 BILLION DURING THE THREE MONTHS ENDED

JUNE 30, 2012, REDUCING OSDS GOODWILL FROM $6.4 BILLION TO $223 MILLION.

